$ (beginning of 12th @fsux{kirugu})

@(H.M.1 = 1-8) Lady @wDN{Inana} whose greatness is vaster than the mountains, hovering like @wDN{An}, vested with grandeur like @wDN{Enlil}, like her father, perfect by night and in the heat of the day, like @wDN{Utu}, surpassing in vigour, singularly exalted in all the four regions -- let @wRN{Išme-@wDN{Dagan}} take pleasure in relaxing in your temple, let him murmer to you in your temple, let him raise his head to you in your @wTN{E-ana}.

@(H.M.9 = 9-19) Let @wRN{Išme-@wDN{Dagan}} serve you as your steward. Let him prepare great bulls for you. Let him dedicate great offerings to you. Let him make the beer, fat and oil plentiful for you. Let him make syrup and wine flow for you as from stone jars. Let @wRN{Išme-@wDN{Dagan}}, son of @wDN{Enlil} on the king's pedestal, bow in homage to you. May he make the @fsux{ub} and @fsux{ala} drums resound grandly for you. May the @fsux{tigi} sound sweetly for you, and may the @fsux{zamzam} play for you. May they play …… on the @fsux{tigi} for you, expressing your prayers and supplications before you.

@(H.M.20 = 20-27) In bringing forth ……, all that there are, at your @wTN{E-ŋipar} in @wSN{Unug}, as a humble man who has grasped your feet, as a reverent man who has experienced your exaltedness, he has brought a lament as offering to you and will ……. As for everything that happened to @wGN{Sumer} and @wGN{Akkad}, which he has witnessed in @wSN{Unug}, the aggrieved place, may the best singers perform songs there.

@(H.M.28 = 28-38) If the @wDN{Anuna} gods emerge tearfully, let them promise to us that as it was when heaven and earth came about, nothing of that time shall be changed. If @wDN{An} looks kindly upon that man and at the well-built city, the place of determining fate, proclaim @q[Inana,]{“Man and city! Life and well-being!”} for him. Let praise ring out. Let him be made surpassing above all, to his right or left. Tireless @fsux{lamma} deity, take hold of his head, pronounce his fate in charitable words -- by the command of @wDN{An} and @wDN{Enlil} it will remain unaltered for a long time.

